Name: TAB BIRTHDAY CARD STAKES
RaceComment: Typically open mare's race. ZAPATEO (3) was a touch disappointing first up in the Oakleigh Plate when beaten 4.5 lengths but did start 9-1 there in a much tougher race. Back to her own sex with McDonald on, she looks a key chance. JAL LEI (5) was a shock winner of the G3 Weona Girl Quality first up. It's worth noting she started 40-1 behind ZAPATEO (7-1) when they clashed at Flemington last time in, but her win fresh was good. JUMP THE BROOM (6) lost the Weona Girl on protest having shifted out badly late. She's consistent and in the mix again. HYPOTHETICAL (14) was a smart winner when well fancied at Randwick Kensington last start and drops sharply in weight. Should give a sight. PALAISIPAN (1) has plenty of class and was very good behind Shades Of Rose over this track and trip first up last time in.

Runners.Name: Palaisipan
Runners.Owners: Mrs C Munce, W B Andrews Breeding & Racing, Murrumba, K H Walsh, Mrs T M O'grady, Ms A Brynza, R J Gall, L J Thompson & F Mazza
Runners.Colours: ROYAL BLUE, YELLOW HOOPS, ARMBANDS, HOOPED CAP
Runners.RunnerComment: Has won previously first-up and resumes here after a break of four-and-a-half months. Finished off last campaign second last of 16 at Flemington in the G1 Empire Rose October 29 over 1600m, soft track; 7 len behind Icebath carrying 57kg at $17. When resuming last campaign third of 12 at this track in the G2 Sheraco September 10 over 1200m, 0.9 len behind Shades Of Rose carrying 56kg at $19. Looks forward enough after a recent trial win. Expect a bold showing.

Runners.Name: Sky Command
Runners.Owners: B Vieira, Mrs S G Vieira, T Vieira, Mrs R Vieira, Mrs C Vieira-Choy, J A Choy & Vieira Racing (Mgr: B Vieira)
Runners.Colours: Black, Gold Vee, Striped Sleeves, Quartered Cap
Runners.RunnerComment: Second-up. First-up after three months sat on the pace before fading 7th of 9 at Randwick in the G3 Wenonagirl on March 4 over 1200m, on a slow track; 2.75 len behind Jal Lei carrying 56.5kg at $3. Previously second-up 8th of 12 at this track in the G2 Sheraco on September 10 over 1200m, 3 len behind Shades Of Rose with 54kg at $26. Don't underestimate.

Runners.Name: Zapateo
Runners.RunnerComment: Second-up. First-up after four months 12th of 16 at Sandown-Lakeside in the G1 Oakleigh Plt on February 25 over 1100m, 4.5 len behind Uncommon James carrying 52kg at $10. Previously second-up 6th of 8 at Randwick in the G3 Concorde on September 3 over 1000m, in the wet; 6 len behind Eduardo with 56kg at $6. Among the top chances.

Runners.Name: Jal Lei
Runners.Owners: W Duck Pty Ltd (Mgr: A D Paradice)

PreviousForm.Comment: Blinkers Again Began Awkwardly. Taken Back From Wide Barrier. Laid In In Straight.

Runners.RunnerComment: Second-up. First-up after four months came from midfield and won by a nose at Randwick G3 Wenonagirl March 4 over 1200m on a soft track defeating Tycoon Evie with 53kg at $13. Previously second-up settled towards the rear 2nd of 10 (began awkwardly; taken back from wide barrier; laid in in the straight) at Randwick Kensington Bm72 on June 29 over 1250m, on a slow track; nose behind Dalaalaat carrying 58kg at $4.80. Improver who is an excellent winning chance.

Runners.Name: Jump The Broom
Runners.RunnerComment: Third-up today. First-up rolled along in front before being edged out 2nd of 11 at Randwick in the G3 Triscay on February 11 over 1200m, 1.2 len behind Po Kare Kare carrying 54kg at $9.50. Second-up tried to lead throughout but was claimed late 3rd of 9 at Randwick in the G3 Wenonagirl on March 4 over 1200m, on a slow track; 0.8 len behind Jal Lei with 53kg at $8. Has the ability to take this out.

Runners.Name: Written Beauty
Runners.Colours: White, Red Star, Yellow Stars Sleeves, Red Star On Cap
Runners.RunnerComment: Third-up today and won third-up in the past. First-up eased back early on 7th of 11 at Randwick in the G3 Triscay on February 11 over 1200m, 2.5 len behind Po Kare Kare carrying 55.5kg at $6. Second run from a spell 4th of 9 at Randwick in the G3 Wenonagirl on March 4 over 1200m, slow going 2 len behind Jal Lei with 53kg at $9.50. Not far away last start. Big chance.

Runners.Name: Barossa Rosa
Runners.Owners: A K C Thoroughbreds (Mgr: Mrs K Chrysiliou)
Runners.RunnerComment: Last start raced on the pace before fading second last of 9 at Randwick in the G3 Wenonagirl on March 4 over 1200m, on a slow track; 2.75 len behind Jal Lei with 54kg at $6. Before that tracked the speed and boxed on steadily 4th of 14 at Gold Coast Mm F&M on January 19 over 1300m, on a slow track; 1.1 len behind Brookspire carrying 56.5kg at $7. Will find this too difficult.

Runners.Name: Nicci's Fling
Runners.Owners: G T Miranda, B P Jessop, C Dallas, P J Fuller, B Childs, P G Stewart, W A Lee, M Phillips, B S C Noney, Promenade Racing (Mgr: Mrs N Savage), Horns Racing (Mgr: R Rowan), Newcombe Turf (Mgr: D Newcombe), Gold Edge (Mgr: C Purcell), Don't Tell The Mrs (Mgr: R Hyslop) & H And M Racing (Mgr: T Mckeon)
Runners.Colours: BLACK, GOLD EDGE SYNDICATION LOGO, EPAULETTES, SEAMS SLEEVES, POM POM
Runners.RunnerComment: At the latest run 3rd in a small field at Kembla Grange Lillye - Bm94 on March 10 over 1200m, 1.1 len behind Bacchanalia carrying 55kg at $4.50. The race before that 2nd of 10 at Randwick Bm88 on February 25 over 1200m, head behind Much Much Better carrying 52.5kg at $26. Not far from the winner last time but this is a tough assignment.

Runners.Name: Ausbred Flirt
Runners.Owners: C J Lawlor, Mrs L C Lawlor & Yes Bloodstock (Mgr: B F Sokolski)
Runners.Colours: Green, Gold Ausbred Logo, Striped Sleeves, Gold Cap

PreviousForm.Comment: Began Awkwardly. Taken Back From Wide Barrier.

Runners.RunnerComment: Dual acceptor. Has won previously first-up and resumes here after a break of 12 weeks. Finished off last campaign second of 8 at Randwick 3&4Y Bm72 December 24 over 1600m, a long neck behind Estadio Mestalla carrying 57kg at $3.80. Previously first up; fifth of 12 at Newcastle Cl1 October 15 over 1200m, soft track; 1.5 len behind Excelladus carrying 56kg at $6.50. Has solid claims while fresh.

Runners.Name: Meg
Runners.Owners: M J Dale, Mrs A E Dale, R K Thompson, C A Fitzgerald, Forbrydelsen Pty Ltd (Mgr: J R Baxter) & M P Lenaghan
Runners.Colours: PINK, DARK BLUE, WHITE CHECKED SASH, SLEEVES, CAP
Runners.RunnerComment: Resuming. Finished off last preparation second last of 14 at Randwick in the G3 Angst October 15 over 1600m, soft track; 9 len behind Hope In Your Heart carrying 55kg at $11. Previous preparation first-up won by a neck Randwick F&M Bm78 August 6 over 1200m slow track defeating Sunrise Ruby carrying 52kg at $41. Will struggle against these.

Runners.Name: Hypothetical
Runners.Owners: Boyd Bloodstock (Mgr: A M Boyd), Yarraman Park Stud (Mgr: A D Mitchell), King Lodge Racing (Mgr: J C King), D J Hall & R W Hill-Smith
Runners.Colours: Royal Blue, Gold Seams, Striped Sleeves, Royal Blue Cap, Gold Seams
Runners.RunnerComment: Third-up today and won third-up previously. Resuming 4th of 8 at this track 3&4Y Bm78 on February 18 over 1100m, 1.75 len behind Parisal carrying 58.5kg at $15. Second run from a spell favourite; won by a long-neck at Randwick Kensington Bm78 March 8 over 1100m defeating Conrad carrying 59.5kg at $2.60. Fitter and should relish the step up to 1200m.

Runners.Name: Duchy Of Savoy
Runners.Owners: Glentree Racing (Mgr: B W C Wilson)
Runners.Colours: Aqua, Pale Blue Diamonds, Diamond Armbands
Runners.RunnerComment: Third-up today and won third-up previously. Resuming came from midfield; 2nd of 7 at Randwick Kensington Bm72 on February 3 over 1000m, 3.5 len behind Insurrection carrying 60.5kg at $3. Second-up ran last of 8 at this track 3&4Y Bm78 on February 18 over 1100m, 7 len behind Parisal with 57kg at $21. Likely to feel the pinch in this company.
